<section id="tech">
<h2> Tech specs</h2>
<div id="l16-layers-wrap" class="scrolly">
<h4 class="tool-tip">Click on a component to learn about its function</h4>
<ul class="l16-layers">
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-1-front-glass.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Front glass</h4>
<p>Gorilla&reg; Glass 4 protects the L16's mirrors and lens modules.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-2-spacer.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Spacer</h4>
<p>This plastic spacer has an adhesive that holds the cover glass to the chassis.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-3-front-grip.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Front grip</h4>
<p>We use a dimpled thermoplastic-polyurethane grip on the front and sides of the L16 so that it never slips out of your hands.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/l16-chassis-400kb.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Chassis</h4>
<p>The L16's durable aluminum unibody frame is cast and machined to ensure proper camera alignment with minimal weight.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-4-side-grip.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Side grip</h4>
<p>The side grip helps photographers hold the L16 comfortably while also allowing GPS/Wi-Fi/BT sensors to communicate with the outside world.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-21-battery.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Battery</h4>
<p>Light's 4120 mAh Lithium-ion polymer battery allows you to take photos all day.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-19-lense-array.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Lens array</h4>
<p>The L16's lens array, a combination of 28mm, 70mm, and 150mm modules, is responsible for shifting the camera's mirrors when the photographer is trying to zoom. Whenever a shot is fired, these lenses work with their respective mirrors and sensors to capture 10+ images, which are later fused together.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-20-accessory-connector.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Accessory connector</h4>
<p>The Light accessory port will be used to connect future add-ons and accessories to the main L16 camera.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-22-main-board.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Mainboard</h4>
<p>The mainboard pairs the Qualcomm Snapdragon 820, 256GB of internal storage, and three custom Light ASICs to make the L16 the most powerful camera ever released.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-23-rear-housing.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Rear housing</h4>
<p>This layer houses the full HD touch screen and an ambient light sensor for adjusting screen brightness. It's primary role, however, is to protect, seal, and shield the LCD touchscreen.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-24-lcm.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">5&quot; Full HD LCD touchscreen</h4>
<p>Similar to the touchscreen you might find in your smart phone, the 5&quot; HD LCD touchscreen is used to operate the L16. This is where you see a live preview when you're zooming in on your scene.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-25-rear-glass.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Rear glass</h4>
<p>Light uses Gorilla&reg; Glass 4 to protect and shield the LCD touchscreen.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-13-antenna-1.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Antenna 1</h4>
<p>The L16 is equipped with a horizontal GPS antenna which allows you to tag the location of your images anywhere, anytime.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-14-antenna-2.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Antenna 3</h4>
<p>The camera's third antenna enables WiFi sharing with another Android or Windows devices.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-15-antenna-3.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Antenna 2</h4>
<p>The L16 is equipped with horizontal Wi-Fi and bluetooth antennas, which allow you to update your camera's software anywhere, anytime.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-16-lanyard-loop.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Lanyard loop</h4>
<p>Attach a wrist or shoulder strap here to avoid ever dropping your L16.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-18-helicoil.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Tripod socket</h4>
<p>Mount your L16 to a standard 1/4&quot;-20 tripod using this socket.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-5-flash-sensor-1.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Front microphone</h4>
<p>Used for recording sound when capturing a video.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-6-flash-sensor-2.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Proximity sensor</h4>
<p>These smart sensors let you know when your fingers are in the L16's field of view.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-7-flash-sensor-3.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">LED Flash and laser-assisted autofocus sensor</h4>
<p>Dual LEDs are used to provide optimal lighting for a scene shot by the L16, while the class 1 laser estimates distance between subject and camera during autofocus.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-8-flash-sensor-4.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Proximity sensor</h4>
<p>These smart sensors let you know when your fingers are in the L16's field of view.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-12-power-button-4.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Electronic shutter button</h4>
<p>The electronic shutter sends a signal to the L16's camera modules, telling them when to fire.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-11-power-button-3.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Illuminated shutter</h4>
<p>The LED light ring positioned around the shutter button illuminates to indicate both power and charge status.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-10-power-button-2.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Power button</h4>
<p>The Power button turns the L16 on and off and puts your preview screen to sleep.</p> </div>
</div>
<li class="spec-item">
<img class="l16-spec-img" src="https://light.co/content/2-camera/l16-layers/layer-9-power-button.png">
</li>
<div class="l16-spec-info">
<div class="info-wrap">
<h4 class="spec_name">Shutter button cap</h4>
<p>When you half-press this metal button, the L16 moves mirrors inside its 10+ camera modules to focus on a subject. Pressing all the way down will fire off the 10+ camera modules simulataneously.</p> </div>
</div>
</ul>
</div>


<div id="tech-spec-accordion">
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Physical</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>Dimensions - H x W x D</b><br> 6.5 x 3.3 x 0.94 in. (165 x 84.5 x 24.05 mm).</li>
<li><b>Weight</b><br> 15.3 oz. (435 g)</li>
<li><b>Chassis</b><br> Die-cast aluminum alloy</li>
<li><b>Grip</b><br> Rubberized non-slip grip with lanyard connection</li>
<li><b>Screen</b><br> 5" FHD touchscreen</li>
<li><b>Tripod mount</b><br> Standard 1/4"-20tpi</li>
<li><b>USB</b><br> USB 3.0 SuperSpeed <br>Type-C connector</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Camera</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>Lenses</b><br> 16 individual modules <br>
5 x 28mm ƒ/2.0, 5 x 70mm ƒ/2.0, and 6 x 150mm ƒ/2.4 <br>
Focal lengths at full frame equivalent</li>
<li><b>Sensors</b><br> 16 individual 13MP sensors</li>
<li><b>Zoom</b><br> 5 x Optical zoom</li>
<li><b>ISO sensitivity</b><br> 100 - 3200</li>
<li><b>Focus</b><br> Minimum: 10cm at 28mm, 40cm at 70mm, 1m at 150mm <br>
Tap to focus <br>
Half-shutter press to focus</li>
<li><b>Shutter speed</b><br> 1/8000 to 15 sec</li>
<li><b>Metering method</b><br> Auto <br> Manual</li>
<li><b>Exposure modes</b><br> 1/8000 to 15 sec</li>
<li><b>Shutter release modes</b><br> Single-frame <br>
Self-timer <br>
3 and 6 shot burst</li>
<li><b>Flash</b><br> Dual-tone LED (no sync port/shoe)</li>
 <li><b>Image formats captured</b><br> LRI, JPEG</li>
<li><b>Effective pixels (megapixels)</b><br> Up to 52 million+ (52+ MP)</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Video</b> (coming soon) </h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>4K Video</b><br> 28, 70 or 150mm focal lengths at full frame equivalent</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Software, Hardware, Networking</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>Operating system</b><br> Android</li>
<li><b>Connectivity</b><br> GPS, Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth</li>
<li><b>Security</b><br> Full disk encryption</li>
<li><b>Chip set</b><br> Qualcomm Snapdragon 820 + Light ASIC</li>
<li><b>Battery</b><br> 4120mAh Lithium-ion polymer (up to 8 hours of life)</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Storage</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>Capacity</b><br> 256GB</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Image processing</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>L16 (on device)</b><br> Up to 13MP optimized for social sharing</li>
<li><b>Sharing</b><br> Wi-Fi (on-camera browser)<br>
Bluetooth to Android or Windows <br>
iOS (coming soon) <br>
Direct social integration (coming soon)</li>
<li><b>Lumen (desktop application)</b><br> Process photos <br>
Adjust depth of field <br>
Edit depth <br>
Adjust focal plane</li>
<li><b>Output</b><br> File types: JPEG, DNG</li>
<li><b>System requirements</b><br> 8 GB or more of RAM (16 GB recommended) <br>
200MB of available hard-disk space (1GB recommended) <br>
64-bit processor</li>
<li><b>Mac</b><br> 2012 or newer<br>
OS X version 10.10.5 (Yosemite) or higher</li>
<li><b>PC</b><br> 2012 or newer <br>
Windows 7 (with Service Pack 1),
Windows 8.1, or Windows 10</li>
<li><b>Intel chipset requirements</b><br>
Nehalem, Westmere, Sandy Bridge, Ivy Bridge, Haswell, Broadwell, Skylake
</li>
<li><b>AMD chipset requirements</b><br>
Jaguar, Puma, Bulldozer, Piledriver, Steamroller, Excavator, Zen
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="ts-accordion-title"><b>Environment</b></h3>
<ul class="ts-section-divide">
<li><b>Operating temperatures</b><br> 32 to 104°F (0 to 40°C)</li>
<li><b>Water and dust resistance</b><br> IP52 - Protected from limited dust ingress. Protected from water spray less than 15 degrees from vertical.</li>
</ul>

</ul>
</div>

